  "items": [
    {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::provider_verification_mixed_abstraction_levels",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "Provider verification APIs expose three different contract layers for the same job",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/GoogleTokenVerifier.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/MicrosoftTokenVerifier.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/ProviderIdentityNormalizer.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/OAuth2SuccessHandler.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/AuthController.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`GoogleTokenVerifier.verify(String)` returns the vendor-specific `GoogleIdToken.Payload`, and callers then unpack fields to call `ProviderIdentityNormalizer.normalizeGoogleClaims(String googleId, String email, String name, String pictureUrl, AuthFlow loginFlow)`.",
          "`MicrosoftTokenVerifier.verifyIdToken(String credential, String expectedNonce, AuthFlow authFlow)` already returns `NormalizedIdentity`, while `ProviderIdentityNormalizer.normalizeMicrosoftClaims(Map<String, Object> claims, AuthFlow loginFlow)` accepts a raw claims map on other code paths.",
          "Similar 'verify an identity and hand it to user creation' flows therefore make callers remember three different public contract shapes: provider payload, raw claim map, and already-normalized domain object."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Choose one public contract level for provider adapters\u2014either have both verifiers return `NormalizedIdentity`, or have both expose typed raw claims and let one normalizer own the mapping\u2014so Google and Microsoft flows can be used with the same mental model.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "2f0f4296"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
      "primary_command": "desloppify plan resolve \"review::.::holistic::api_surface_coherence::provider_verification_mixed_abstraction_levels\" --note \"<what you did>\" --confirm",
      "queue_position": 9,
      "plan_cluster": {
        "name": "abstraction-alignment",
        "description": "Align provider verifier abstractions",
        "total_items": 3,
        "action_steps": [
          {
            "title": "Make GoogleTokenVerifier return NormalizedIdentity",
            "effort": "medium"
          },
          {
            "title": "Remove Google SDK import from AuthController",
            "effort": "small"
          },
          {
            "title": "Improve AuthenticatedUserIdentity typing",
            "effort": "medium"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::dependency_health::google_api_client_leaks_into_auth_flow",
      "confidence": "high",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "Google verification ties the auth flow to the broad google-api-client library",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "dependency_health",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/pom.xml",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/GoogleTokenVerifier.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/AuthController.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/MicrosoftTokenVerifier.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`backend/pom.xml` adds `com.google.api-client:google-api-client` as a dedicated runtime dependency for Google token verification.",
          "`GoogleTokenVerifier.java` uses that library only to build `GoogleIdTokenVerifier` and returns `GoogleIdToken.Payload` directly to callers.",
          "`AuthController.java` imports `com.google.api.client.googleapis.auth.oauth2.GoogleIdToken` and works with the vendor payload in web-layer code, so the dependency is not confined to a single adapter.",
          "By contrast, `MicrosoftTokenVerifier.java` translates vendor JWT data into app-local `NormalizedIdentity`, showing the Google path is more dependency-coupled than the rest of the auth stack."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Keep Google SDK usage inside `GoogleTokenVerifier` by translating verified claims into an app-local DTO or `NormalizedIdentity` before returning, and when this path is next touched evaluate replacing `google-api-client` with a narrower Google token-verification library so the auth subsystem depends on less vendor surface area.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "608c44f3"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
      "primary_command": "desloppify plan resolve \"review::.::holistic::dependency_health::google_api_client_leaks_into_auth_flow\" --note \"<what you did>\" --confirm",
      "queue_position": 10,
