    {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::authenticated_user_identity_nullable_union",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "AuthenticatedUserIdentity mixes legacy and v2 identities in one nullable record",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/AuthenticatedUserIdentity.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/JwtTokenService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/UserService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/UserController.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`AuthenticatedUserIdentity.legacy(...)` creates a record with null `userId`, `provider`, `providerUserId`, and `contractVersion`, while `v2(...)` nulls `legacyGoogleId`, so valid state depends on knowing which factory built the instance rather than on the type itself.",
          "`JwtTokenService.parseAuthenticatedUser(...)` returns both legacy and v2 identities through that same record, and `UserService.findCurrentUser(...)` has to branch on `identity.isLegacy()` to decide whether email or user ID is authoritative.",
          "`UserController.getCurrentUser(...)` fabricates a legacy `AuthenticatedUserIdentity` from `authentication.getName()` when the principal is untyped, which shows the abstraction leaking across the controller/service boundary instead of presenting one stable principal contract."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split the principal model into two explicit identity types behind a tiny common interface, or at minimum split the downstream lookup APIs so callers do not pass around a record whose meaningful fields depend on `contractVersion` and null sentinels.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "f049e417"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
      "primary_command": "desloppify plan resolve \"review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::authenticated_user_identity_nullable_union\" --note \"<what you did>\" --confirm",
